&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Tucson listens with a deep intensity and closes his optics to allow for
&gt; better audio performance.  Sounds become sharper and easier to hear.  Being
&gt; blind for nearly his entire existence further enhances his ability to
&gt; compensate for not having his sense of sight.  Gently he places one palm on
&gt; the wall, and then concentrates on what he feels on the bottom of his feet
&gt; and on the palms of his hands.  He takes a deep breath in to catch any scent
&gt; that may seem different to the scents around him.  And finally uses his
&gt; sense of thermal  registering which is felt through the nostrils of his
&gt; somewhat draconic facial features.  It was how a snake would detect it&#39;s
&gt; prey and the same held true for other reptiles.  He narrows an optic and
&gt; speaks with a whisper.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Night Viper, wait.  Something doesn&#39;t feel right.  I&#39;m picking up
&gt; vibrations through the wall and my thermal imaging system is detecting an
&gt; unknown entity.  You&#39;re reptilian derived as well, see if you can detect the
&gt; same as I .&quot;
&gt;
&gt; Tucson moves in closer to protect the smaller Maximals from harm.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; If someone is following us we must move cautiously.&quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

NIGHT VIPER froze in place, his body rigid as he strained his sensors
to the maximum. &quot;I am picking up something as well.&quot; VIPER said, his
voice speculative and then urgent. &quot;Perhaps it is one of the
auxilliary motors that vent these tunnels?&quot;

&quot; I hope so.&quot; BIG CONVOY said from above, &quot;Our armament stash is
below, if they find us before we can get down there then we will be
largely defenseless.&quot; There was a small grunt, &quot;Hand to hand is
useless if your opponant is out of easy range.&quot;

